article.headline: Columbia 65, Dartmouth 52
article.story: NEW YORK -- Noruwa Agho scored 20 points and Jason Miller added 19 points and Columbia defeated Dartmouth 65-52 on Friday night for the Lions' fourth win in five games. Columbia (9-12, 4-3 Ivy League) opened the second half with a 15-2 run after taking a 29-27 lead at the half on K.J. Matsui's 3-pointer at the buzzer. Matsui finished with 11 points. Alex Barnett led the Big Green with 20 points while Robby Pride and David Rufful scored 10 points apiece. Dartmouth, which had won four of five, fell to 6-15 overall and 4-2 in the conference. Columbia scored the first 10 points of the second half to open a 39-27 lead with Agho scoring six. After Barnett's jumper stopped the opening run, Miller hit two inside shots wrapped around a 3-pointer from Matsui to give the Lions the game's biggest lead at 46-29 with 13:59 remaining.
